folder: 7th Avenue South & Grove Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Seventh Avenue South, east side, and 76-70 Grove Street, at and south of the Sheridan Square subway station at West 4th Street. The subway entrance is in a little island which used to be the N.W. corner of Grove (formerly Burrows Street, originally Columbia Street) and West 4th (formerly Asylum Street) Streets. Sheridan Square (q.v.) is properly the triangular open space shown here in the left background, but it is loosely applied to both sides of Seventh Avenue South, from Christopher to Grove Streets, inclusive.
About 1928.

Ewing Galloway.

folder: Grove Street & 7th Avenue South, Manhattan, NY
text:
Grove Street, southerly side, east from Seventh Avenue South (right, not included), showing buildings thereupon, as viewed across the open triangular park at Christopher Street. In the center is the gap formed by the convergence of Washington Place and West 4th Street, and known as Sheridan Square. The photographer details the restaurant-bar of Jack Delaney in View 2. This adjoins the corner of Seventh Avenue.
June 6, 1940
No's. 1-2
P. L. Sperr
